		<item>
		<title>FOCUS Your, appointments, questions, time &#038; proposals</title>
		<link>http://www.adsalestips.com/focus-your-appointments-questions-time-proposals/</link>
		<comments>http://www.adsalestips.com/focus-your-appointments-questions-time-proposals/#respond</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 17 Sep 2015 13:55:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[morris]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.adsalestips.com/?p=2409</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Todays advertising sales professional is fighting in the trenches each day to close deals, its very common for a advertising sales person to develop a thick [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Todays advertising sales professional is fighting in the trenches each day to close deals, its very common for a advertising sales person to develop a thick skin, given that we hear the words ‘no’ before we get a yes. In today’s recovering market not every brand is buying. Having said all that, This year has been our best year in 15 years, we have broken all print, digital &#038; web advertising targets, why? The year we recruited 1 additional area manager with a great deal of experience to match the current teams experience, skills and qualities, we then split the markets to allow each area manager to ‘FOCUS’</p>
<p>Lets talk about that word ‘FOCUS’ advertising sales requires ‘FOCUS’ we need to make sure thats we understand which prospects can invest against the prospects that have a budget freeze. Then it is vital that we ask the right questions, todays success is giving our clients exactly what they are looking for and delivering it. It is possible to convert all your appointments into sales if you listen to what they want.</p>
<p>The proposal should not be an effort to sell everything from your portfolio, brands have budget to spend on the things they need and want, so its simple, ‘sell them what they need’</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.adsalestips.com/focus-your-appointments-questions-time-proposals/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Struggling to sell advertising?</title>
		<link>http://www.adsalestips.com/struggling-to-sell-advertising/</link>
		<comments>http://www.adsalestips.com/struggling-to-sell-advertising/#respond</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2015 13:53:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[morris]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.adsalestips.com/?p=2407</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Never loose belief in yourself! Always go back to your basic training, leverage all your experience and think back to all your successes and glorious advertising [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Never loose belief in yourself!</p>
<p>Always go back to your basic training, leverage all your experience and think back to all your successes and glorious advertising sales deals. When selling media or advertising the market conditions and your product or service are the main factors, ok, they say never to blame your tools, but, in todays market conditions, the targets requirements are changing, more and more people are using multi-platforms at different times of the day depending on what they are doing, this means the product or service you are selling needs to adapt and change for todays target audience, advertisers are under extreme pressure to get a return on their investment, which is correct, so, help them.</p>
<p>What happens if you stay static and reluctant to make the necessary changes?</p>
<p>The answer is simple, slowly you will loose clients and the up hill struggle begins. A great sales person listens to what clients want and to the market conditions, this means a sales person should be free to sell the perfect solution for that client , if you are struggling to provide clients what they are looking for then you have two simple decisions to make:</p>
<p>• Adapt your product or service accordingly<br />
• Cut your losses and find a product or service you truly believe in selling</p>
<p>Sales can be very rewarding, but only when all the elements meet, the product or service needs to meet the clients requirements and get results to deliver client satisfaction. Only then can you feel light and nimble to get the desired results for your and your product.</p>
<p>I have worked in many blue chip media companies and now have my own media company, I have always said that the hardest role in the company is the sales role, sales are the tip of the sword that can make the difference between winning and loosing, all the other departments need to work in sync to be able to service the sales team so that they can get the best results for the whole company.</p>
<p>Stand up and be counted, as a sales person you are the front line of any media company, don’t be afraid to tell your team mates what needs to change in order to get the best results.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.adsalestips.com/struggling-to-sell-advertising/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
