		<item>
		<title>KEEP YOUR EYE ON THE PRIZE</title>
		<link>http://www.adsalestips.com/keep-your-eye-on-the-prize/</link>
		<comments>http://www.adsalestips.com/keep-your-eye-on-the-prize/#respond</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Aug 2014 13:39:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[morris]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.adsalestips.com/?p=2403</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[In advertising sales we are always working to deadlines, be it a print deadline, a simple campaign or an annual target; it is always important to [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In advertising sales we are always working to deadlines, be it a print deadline, a simple campaign or an annual target; it is always important to remain focused and keep your eye on the prize. Personally I always have all my prospects up on a big board with the names of the potential advertisers and the $ amount along side; as each deal is closed I use a thick red marker and write “booked”, plus I make a tick alongside the advertiser. At the top of the board I have the revenue target and alongside a running total of sales paid to date. I am 100% focused on reaching that target, if I start to see some crosses rather than ticks that motivates me to find even more prospects.</p>
<p>I also have become very disciplined schedule-wise, as the years go by: in the morning I check my emails, and double check my replies very carefully, I then focus on new business development, which means booking new appointments and looking for new prospects; around 4pm I change my frame of mind and work on my proposals.</p>
<p>When it comes to working on my proposals I have learnt to personalize each one of them, I really take the time to tailor each proposal making sure that it’s perfect for each client: once I send the proposal by email I make a note in my agenda of when it was sent, and then mark a date for the follow-up (normally one week after the first email). I then follow up with a call or a second email, depending on the client’s availability. Once a proposal has been sent I follow that proposal like a hound and make sure I get a reply. Of course if the reply is positive great! If not then I need to ask questions as to why my offer was not agreeable and look to adapt the proposal in order to close the sale.</p>
<p>Being focused is vital, making sure you as an advertising sales person are effective each day. If you are disciplined, focused, you will never get distracted from the goal at hand.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.adsalestips.com/keep-your-eye-on-the-prize/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Selling print &#038; digital advertising is the winning formula now and moving forward</title>
		<link>http://www.adsalestips.com/selling-print-digital-advertising-is-the-winning-formula-now-and-moving-forward/</link>
		<comments>http://www.adsalestips.com/selling-print-digital-advertising-is-the-winning-formula-now-and-moving-forward/#respond</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 23 Jun 2014 13:36:46 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[morris]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.adsalestips.com/?p=2401</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[In most cases today&#8217;s advertisers have a print campaign that will follow with a digital campaign shortly after, today&#8217;s advertisers are far more likely to invest [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In most cases today&#8217;s advertisers have a print campaign that will follow with a digital campaign shortly after, today&#8217;s advertisers are far more likely to invest in a multi-platform that is fully integrated. The info graphic images show a hypothetical example following:<br />
<span id="more-2401"></span></p>
<p>• Editorial in print: By placing a QRcode on the print editorial it is then possible to link the editorial to a landing page or the digital magazine or their website<br />
• The Digital magazine: Digital adverts can have both embedded video for longer reader engagement and link the advert back to a landing page or the advertiser&#8217;s website<br />
• Web: It is important today that your website is responsive so that your content can be read on any device and interconnects with your other platforms<br />
• Newsletters: Excellent tool that can be linked back to a landing page or the advertiser&#8217;s site, plus inviting subscribers to an Event</p>
<p>Advertisers prefer to buy a package which includes print, digital &amp; web advertising that can be tracked, editorial support which can appear on all platforms &amp; social media which can also be tracked, &amp; client events; finally a report should be produced at the end of the campaign which can clearly show where all the traffic came from and from which platforms.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.adsalestips.com/selling-print-digital-advertising-is-the-winning-formula-now-and-moving-forward/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
		</item>
		<item>
		<title>Does a BPA audited help you sell more advertising?</title>
		<link>http://www.adsalestips.com/does-a-bpa-audited-help-you-sell-more-advertising/</link>
		<comments>http://www.adsalestips.com/does-a-bpa-audited-help-you-sell-more-advertising/#respond</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 16 Apr 2014 13:34:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[morris]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.adsalestips.com/?p=2399</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[My own brand LUXOS has been a controlled circulation title for 14 years and as we have a severe distribution monitoring system we have never felt [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My own brand LUXOS has been a controlled circulation title for 14 years and as we have a severe distribution monitoring system we have never felt the need to have our print, web &amp; digital products audited, however, more and more media agencies play a bigger role in where the brand invests their budget. Media agencies like to tick the boxes and one of those ticks is that a title must be BPA audited in order to advance to the next round of talks. I recently sent out the official communication to all our clients about this new BPA and while I am sure nothing would have changed should we not signed up to be BPA stamped, I did see a relief in our clients replies, it seems to put any doubts that could have been in the air to rest. Let me know your comments and I invite you to share your experience in the subject</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.adsalestips.com/does-a-bpa-audited-help-you-sell-more-advertising/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
